OL,3,CSycamore Gap sapling stolen from Lake
OL,4,CDistrict
OL,6,FA sapling which was taken from the
OL,7,Ffelled Sycamore Gap Tree has been
OL,8,Fstolen from the grounds of a castle in
OL,9,Fthe Lake District.
OL,11,FIt was planted at Wray Castle, near
OL,12,FAmbleside in April 2026 and it's
OL,13,Fbelieved it was stolen last month.
OL,15,FThe saplings ` 49 to mark the
OL,16,Fsycamore's height in feet when it was
OL,17,Fcut down ` were grown from the seeds
OL,18,Fand material rescued from the felled
OL,19,Ftree, which grew on land in
OL,20,FNorthumberland cared for by the
OL,21,FNational Trust.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/5
